                    <p rend="flushleft">I. <hi rend="italic">Report by the Deputies</hi></p>
                    <p>The Council heard the report submitted by the Acting Chairman of the Deputies
                        (See <gloss target="#t_CFMD46NY1">CFM(D) (46) (NY)</gloss> 124th
                            Meeting).<note n="4" xml:id="d371fn4"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1355">p. 1355</ref>.</note></p>
                    <p>The question of the powers of the Provisional Council of Government was
                        re-examined and after a further exchange of views a redraft of the text on
                        this subject was provisionally <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> (with a
                        reservation by the U.K. Delegate—see Annex), and was referred to the
                        Deputies for consideration together with the U.S. and U.K. proposals
                        contained in documents <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM(46) (NY)</gloss> 22
                        and 23 respectively, the French draft instructions to the Governor and the
                        special question dealt with in the U.K. memorandum of August 29, 1946 (Doc.
                            <gloss target="#t_CFM461">CFM (46)</gloss>258).<note n="5" xml:id="d371fn5">Locations of the documents under reference in this
                            paragraph are indicated in the document cited in footnote 4
                            above.</note></p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">II. <hi rend="italic">Questions Outstanding on the Peace
                            Treaties</hi><note n="6" xml:id="d371fn6">Individual articles referred
                            to in this section are identified in greater detail in the United States
                            Delegation Minutes, <hi rend="italic">supra.</hi></note></p>
                    <p>The Council resumed consideration item by item of the list of unsettled
                        questions in the various Treaty texts.</p>
                    <pb facs="1392" n="1368" xml:id="pg_1368"/>
                    <p>(1) <hi rend="italic">Settlement of Economic Disputes</hi></p>
                    <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to adopt the Soviet Delegation’s
                        proposal for this Article in the various treaties as modified by the
                        original U.S. amendment under which the Secretary-General of the United
                        Nations instead of the President of the International Court of Justice would
                        nominate an arbitrator. It was further <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> that
                        Article 72 in the Italian Treaty should also include paragraphs (<hi rend="italic">b</hi>) to (<hi rend="italic">g</hi>) of the Conference
                        recommendation on this Article. Final formulation of the relevant texts was
                        entrusted to the Economic Experts.</p>
                    <p>(2) <hi rend="italic">Enemy Assets in the Territory of the Allied and
                            Associated Powers</hi></p>
                    <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to bring the text of Article 25 in the
                        Hungarian Treaty into line with that of the corresponding Article in the
                        Roumanian Treaty.</p>
                    <p>The decision regarding Article 24 of the Bulgarian Treaty was <hi rend="italic">deferred.</hi></p>
                    <p>(3) <hi rend="italic">Return of Jewish Property</hi></p>
                    <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to accept the first paragraphs of
                        Article 24A of the Roumanian Treaty, and of Article 23A of the Hungarian
                        Treaty subject to the substitution of “fair compensation” for “full
                        compensation”, and to defer decision on the second paragraphs of those
                        Articles.</p>
                    <p>(4) <hi rend="italic">Rail Traffic</hi></p>
                    <p>The Paris Conference recommendations for the texts of Article 28 bis in the
                        Bulgarian and Article 29 bis in the Hungarian Treaty were <hi rend="italic">adopted.</hi></p>
                    <p>(5) <hi rend="italic">Fair Prices for Reparation Deliveries</hi></p>
                    <p>Decision <hi rend="italic">deferred.</hi></p>
                    <p>(6) <hi rend="italic">Danube-Sava-Adriatic Railway</hi></p>
                    <p>It was <hi rend="italic">agreed</hi> to accept the text of Article 23, para.
                        9 of the Hungarian Treaty in the same wording as Annex III, para. 10 of the
                        Italian Treaty (See Doc. <gloss target="#t_CFM46NY1">CFM (46)
                            (NY)</gloss>30).<note n="7" xml:id="d371fn7"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_1296">p. 1296</ref>.</note></p>
                    <p>(7) <hi rend="italic">Shipping</hi></p>
                    <p>Decision <hi rend="italic">deferred.</hi></p>
                    <p>(8) <hi rend="italic">Interpretation</hi></p>
                    <p>Decision <hi rend="italic">deferred.</hi></p>
                    <p>(9) <hi rend="italic">Motor Torpedo Boats</hi></p>
                    <p>Decision <hi rend="italic">deferred.</hi></p>
                    <p rend="flushleft">III. <hi rend="italic">Next Meeting:</hi></p>
                    <p>of the Council, Monday, December 2nd, at 4 p.m.;</p>
                    <p>of the Deputies, Monday, December 2nd, at 11 a.m.</p>
